The paper deals with communication and information theory, specifically addressing the problem of achieving omniscience in a network. This falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves algorithms and optimization techniques, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with communication networks, which could place it under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
